A blind boy sat on the steps of a building with a hat by his feet. He held up a sign which read, “I am blind, please help.”

There were only a few coins in the hat – spare change from folks as they hurried past.

A man was walking by. He took a few coins from his pocket and dropped them into the hat. He then took the sign, turned it around, and wrote some words. Then he put the sign back in the boy’s hand so that everyone who walked by would see the new words.

Soon the hat began to fill up. A lot more people were giving money to the blind boy.

That afternoon, the man who had changed the sign returned to see how things were. The boy recognized his footsteps and asked, “Were you the one who changed my sign this morning? What did you write?”

The man said, “I only wrote the truth. I said what you said but in a different way.”

I wrote, “Today is a beautiful day, but I cannot see it.”

Both signs spoke the truth. But the first sign simply said the boy was blind, while the second sign conveyed to everyone walking by how grateful they should be to see…

When your life seems full of troubles, it seems difficult to maintain an attitude of gratitude, doesn’t it? All we see are our problems, like a blackened storm cloud casting a dark shadow over our lives.

And the times when everything just seems to be going smoothly? We often take these precious moments for granted too, don’t we? Caught up in the bliss, comfort, and familiarity of it all, we can simply forget to be thankful. 

🤙🏽🙏🏼🫶🏽⚡️💚💯

⚡️Issa Vibe ⚡️

Throwin’ it back to last year’s @beyondthemusicretreat in Arizona. 

For this trip I stepped out of my comfort zone and decided to invest in my passion & see what this event was all about. It became one of the most dopest and inspirational things I did in my DJ career and wish I did something like this sooner. Representing these little islands in the pacific was an honor and It was really cool having a chance to break the ice and introduce myself to over a hundred DJ’s from all over the globe. I have so much more pictures to share!

The craziest part is still being in touch with a lot of these DJs and seeing how much we all grew since that amazing get together. I’m looking forward to more events like this, building real relationships/networking with like-minded people is everything! I’m super thankful for these opportunities and can’t wait for the next ones. 

#TBT #throwbackthursdays #DJs #DJlife #beyondthemusicretreat #djcity

The concept of @ifcancanhawaii is to bring people together for a good cause. Show up to the beach with your can goods & enjoy the rest of the day with friends & family. Its so easy to join the fun!

Whether it was through volunteering your time, donating resources, or spreading the word, each and every one of you played a crucial role in making this event possible. Your collective efforts have had a profound impact on the lives of those in need, and for that, we are incredibly grateful.

From our first event goal of 200 lbs, to our last event that collected over 2,600 lbs of canned goods, (which was donated directly to the @hawaiifoodbank ) it just shows that when we come together, we can achieve extraordinary things.

Let us continue to work together to create a brighter future and uplift those in need. Stay Tuned for details about our next event!

Please Follow @ifcancanhawaii to join the movement of creating memories for a good cause. 🤙🏽

Tag friends & if there are any business that want to get involved please DM me!

Our 6th Annual Event is Sunday November 19th 
Mark your calendar and stay tuned for more details!

Where do I begin?!…😮‍💨

After surpassing 200 shows for 2024, I first want to thank each and every person who has supported & continues to support me in any type of way. This industry is built on support and how you treat others. With that being said, I’m thankful for all the real relationships that grew and for the fake ones that were so easily forgotten. 

2023 was all about consistency for me. I committed to 52 weeks of Mashup Mondays which has been such a positive influence, but also has been so much work. The positive feedback is what kept me going and inspires me to create more. I’m looking to change things up so stay ready. 

This year I had the opportunity to open up for some big artists & venues like Pitbull & Common Kings at the Blaisdell and Kolohe Kai & Matisyahu at the Waikiki Shell. Performing in my hometown of Kona Town was a huge check off the bucket list too. I know that having a good dj & setting the tone for these big shows helps the full experience of an event to make it more memorable and I will continue to show Hawaii that difference. 

Being a full time dj for the past 14 years & traveling the world has been incredible. Unfortunately this industry requires you to be a Music Producer, Graphic Designer, Video Editor, Web Programmer, Content Creator, Social Networking Master, Public Relations Manager, Promoter, Business Negotiator, Booking Agent, oh and of course.. DJ! 😆

Also doing it from a little rock in the middle of an ocean can be quite a challenge. Thats why when there is any love/support coming my way I really do appreciate it a lot! Fr Fr 💯🤙🏽🫶🏽

Cheers! 🍻 to a New Year & New Goals! 
🙌🏼 I’ve been ready for 2024, Let’s Fckn Get It! ⚡️
